# Layer 1 jargon list (csam_jargon.txt) — NOT shipped in this repo.
#
# One term per line. Blank lines and lines starting with '#' are ignored.
# Terms are matched case-insensitively against filenames.
#
# Classification is automatic, by term length:
#   * 6+ characters  -> substring match (matches anywhere in the filename).
#                       Use only for terms that never occur inside innocent
#                       words.
#   * 1-5 characters -> word-boundary match (must be delimited by non-word
#                       characters on both sides), to avoid false positives
#                       such as a short token appearing inside a normal word.
#
# Source your terms from authoritative bodies — INHOPE, IWF, NCMEC — which
# curate indicator lists vetted for low false-positive rates. Do NOT invent
# terms ad hoc.
#
# Absent or empty -> Layer 1 is inactive; Layers 2-4 still run. Hot-reloadable:
# edit this file and changes apply within ~30s, no restart.
#
# (Intentionally empty — populate locally; this .example is a template only.)
